The '''Surveillance Camera Code of Practice''' is a [[code of practice]] devoted to the operation of [[CCTV]] systems in the [[United Kingdom]]. It was introduced under Section 30 (1) (a) of the [[Protection of Freedoms Act 2012]].
The office of the [[Surveillance Camera Commissioner]] was created to support it.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-23636462|title=Surveillance camera code of practice comes into force|date=2013-08-12|work=BBC News|access-date=2017-06-29|language=en-GB}}</ref>
